{
  "stem": "2353.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were able to communicate with each other after a while.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when he told me about the discrimination against black, then they were Negroes, I was so shocked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, how can this be in this country of the free?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How can they discriminate against the people of a different color?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was hard for me to accept.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I found that there was more discrimination-- or not-- not, maybe not discrimination but separation between Jewish people and Gentile people in this country than it was ever in Germany before Hitler came in.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, I never heard of such a thing, that-- that a Jew couldn't join a golf club or any kind of-- the New York Athletic Club, they didn't take Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This to me was-- was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] So-- but you get used to everything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we lived in Texas for awhile when my husband was in the army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we got into terrible fights with people about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I met my husband-- oh, this was another one of those German things, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There must've been a lot of propaganda, again, against coming to-- to have the-- the Americans come-- come to the Olympics.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they arranged to have the best Jewish athletes come to a place and give them-- you know, to see if they could find another athlete who could compete in the Olympics.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they knew very well that there wasn't any.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They might have been the best Jewish athletes, but there wasn't one-- there wasn't a one good enough to compete in the Olympics.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they knew it very well, but it was just a-- a deception to-- to fool the other countries, again.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that's where I met my husband.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
